reviews.title: There are better products in the VEATOOL range.
reviews.review_text: I wanted to love these. I really did. I'd previously owned two sets of X08's, one failed (one earpiece broke), the other set's going strong. So I do appreciate the VEATOOL brand and their reliable/affordable set of products When I seen these, I thought 'oh this must be the next new thing'. Touch screen, etc. Lets start with some of the more obvious flaws. 1. Frequently disconnects - also very easy to de-pair with the other headset and give you that wonky out of phase audio feeling. 2. Charge lasts about an hour. Makes me think that something's constantly trying to pair or work harder than it needs to, to maintain a connection. I've disabled noise cancelling and graphic equalization. Still doesn't last longer. 3. The textured coating on the earpieces (while nice) can become quite slick and leave you fumbling and accidentally touch the controls on the earpiece when you didn't intend to , cutting off a call or other. 4. Touch screen on case. Nice idea but it is fiddly. Doesn't work well with big thumbs. If you want a basic but reliable model, try the X08. Good battery life, wireless charging and average noise cancelling. I will try other models in their lineup in the future, but I think these ones need some TLC from VEATOOL before they're ready for prime-time.

reviews.title: READ BEFORE PURCHASING
reviews.review_text: Don't believe the 5 star reviews!! This seller is dishonest and scamming people. They've submitted hundreds of AI generated reviews, giving their faulty/defective products 5 stars. I totally fell for it too. I didn't read any of the individual reviews before purchasing. I saw ‚Äúflash deal‚Äù $18.99 product usually worth (supposedly) $90, I saw a rating of 4.5 out of 1,400 reviews, and I read the summary of reviews generated by Walmart's AI bot, that said ‚Äúcustomers rave about this product and how amazing it is..‚Äù etc, etc, etc. So of course I thought I hit the jackpot by finding these ear buds at this price, so I immediately bought 2 pair. (One black case and one with a pink case) After receiving them, I was actually pleasantly surprised with the packaging and nice look and feel of the case and ear buds. I liked that it had a display screen to always show the battery level of the case and each ear bud. They were really easy to pair with my Apple TV. BUT- when I started watching my show while using them‚Ä¶ they were pausing and unpausing my show every few seconds, and completely disconnecting and reconnecting every 30 seconds or so. I'm not even exaggerating. It's so bad that these are completely unusable. I thought maybe the first pair was defective so I opened the second pair and they had the same issues. After all this, I decided to go read some of the hundreds of 5 star reviews. It was obvious that every single 5 star review is fake, AI generated reviews. All of the reviews and very similar in wording and length. Some of the reviews are just complete copies of other ones. All of the 5 star reviews are too perfect. Real people make typing errors, grammar and punctuation errors, spelling errors, and use abbreviations and/or slang. Just read thru a handful of them and you'll see what I mean. This seller should be banned from selling with Walmart. They are scammers and liars. I am embarrassed that I fell for it, but I'm hoping others will see this review and it can help prevent them from being scammed like I was.
